Fig. 2. –

Croton ankeranae
Kainul. 
A.
Flowering

branch with two staminate flowers; 
B.
Staminate flower; 
C.
Pistillate flower. Note bifurcate stigmas and greenish sepals; 
D.
Branch with nearly mature capsule; 
E.
Staminate flower; 
F.
Staminate flower with stamens removed to show the five nectaries; 
G.
Pistillate flower, showing bifurcate stigmas and filamentous structure in the position of petals; 
H.
Pistillate flower with ovary and two sepals removed to show the five nectaries. Note the glandular filament in the petal position.
